content: Hello Tritons! Need a de-stress after midterms? We have the perfect escape for you and your friends! Register now to get your FREE ticket to WellFest at Birch Aquarium on Friday, November 8th! Wellfest is a zero-waste wellness event where you can enjoy a delicious and healthy by UC San Diego catering, take fitness classes and dance the night away among the beautiful La Jolla coastline view, listen to a variety of speakers talk about hot wellness topics, receive useful giveaways and farmer’s market goods that will help you kick off a more sustainable lifestyle, and explore the galleries to learn about the ocean and sea life by competing in a scavenger hunt with your friends! DATE: Friday, November 8th, 2019 TIME: 6:00 p.m. – 10:00 p.m. LOCATION: Birch Aquarium, 2300 Expedition Way, Scripps Institute of Oceanography, La Jolla, CA 92037 TRANSPORTATION: Shuttles will begin pick up and drop off at Rupertus Lane & Mesa Nueva from 5:00 p.m. – 10:30 p.m.

content: Enrollment for Winter Quarter 2020 begins Wednesday, November 6, 2019. The Schedule of Classes is now available! First and Second Pass appointment times are available on WebReg.  Your User ID/PID and Password/PAC are required to login.  Check for holds that may block enrollment in classes and/or payment of fees. Waitlists will be available starting November 18, 2019. Students must be enrolled and paid in full by December 13, 2019 to avoid late fees. Students must be enrolled and paid in full by January 6, 2020 to avoid being dropped from classes and wait lists. Students with permanent and temporary disabilities can make arrangements for accommodations and services upon enrollment. To learn more visit the OSD website at http://osd.ucsd.edu. content: Dear All, My name is Summer Joyce Batasin, and I am the UCSD Innovation Ambassador for the UC Big Ideas Contest this year. The UC Big Ideas Contest is an early-stage, UC-wide competition for students interested in receiving mentorship, support, and up to $20,000 for their social ventures. I would like to cordially invite you all to attend our info-session this Monday, November 4th in Fung Auditorium (Powell-Focht Bioengineering Hall) from 6-7PM. During this session, we will go over an overview of the competition, benefits of participating, as well as requirements for the Contest Pre-proposal, a short, three-page description of your idea (due November 20th) and the first step to being eligible to win funding and support for your innovation. Please check out our website, Facebook page or email me if you have any questions, and I hope to see you at our info-session this Monday!
